        {
            "innerHtml": "This skeletal animation was created in OpenGL 2 using C++ for one of my University courses, <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://www.canterbury.ac.nz/courseinfo/GetCourseDetails.aspx?course=COSC422&occurrence=22S2(C)&year=2022\">COSC 422 (Advanced Computer Graphics)</a>, during Semester 2 of 2022. The project itself received an A+ (95%) grade for the course.",
            "tagName": "p",
            "attributes": [
                {
                    "name": "align",
                    "value": "justify"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "innerHtml": "The scene depicts a robot character walking around a football field. Using the arrow keys, the character can be rotated around while in motion. A BVH mocap file was used for the skeletal animation, and was loaded and animated using <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://www.assimp.org/\">Assimp</a>. The skeletal animation makes use of planar shadows, a hand model with fingers, joint rotations without visible gaps between the mesh surfaces, and various shapes, models, and textures.",
            "tagName": "p",
            "attributes": []
        },
